 private parks and, later, public parks and social housing estates, are analyzed and reassessed in terms of their significance for the history and present of landscape and garden design. The volume is illustrated with a large number of the plans from the important archival find.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aGartenarchitektur. 4aGartendesign. 4aGartengestaltung. 4aGartenkultur. 4aHausgarten. 4aLandschaftsarchitektur. 4aModerne. 4aPark. 4aSozialsiedlung. 4aVillengarten. 4aVolkspark.  aGarden Architect.  aGarden culture.  aGarden design.  aLandscape design.  aModernism.  aPublic garden.  ahouse garden.  apark design.1 aKarn, Susanne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKarn, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLerch, Gabi, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLerch, Gabi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwerin, Sophie von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb0 cprintz978303562429840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783035624304zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035624304zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783035624304/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA